bjects\n\n[source,$lang]\n----\n{@link examples.WebClientExamples#multiGet(io.vertx.ext.web.client.WebClient)}\n----\n\nBeware though that {@link io.vertx.ext.web.client.HttpRequest} instances are mutable.\nTherefore you should call the {@link io.vertx.ext.web.client.HttpRequest#copy()} method before modifying a cached instance.\n\n[source,$lang]\n----\n{@link examples.WebClientExamples#multiGetCopy(io.vertx.ext.web.client.WebClient)}\n----\n\n=== Timeouts\n\nYou can set a connect timeout  for a specific http request using {@link io.vertx.ext.web.client.HttpRequest#connectTimeout(long)}.\n\n[source,$lang]\n----\n{@link examples.WebClientExamples#connectTimeout(io.vertx.ext.web.client.WebClient)}\n----\n\nIf the client cannot obtain a connection to the server within the timeout period an exception will be passed to the response\nhandler.\n\nYou can set an idle timeout  for a specific http request using {@link io.vertx.ext.web.client.HttpRequest#idleTimeout(long)}.\n\n[source,$lang]\n----\n{@link examples.WebClientExamples#idleTimeout(io.vertx.ext.web.client.WebClient)}\n----\n\nIf the request does not return any data within the timeout period an exception will be passed to the response\nhandler.\n\nYou can set both timeouts using {@link io.vertx.ext.web.client.HttpRequest#timeout(long)}\n\n[source,$lang]\n----\n{@link examples.WebClientExamples#timeout(io.vertx.ext.web.client.WebClient)}\n----\n\n\n== Handling http responses\n\nWhen the Web Client sends a request you always deal with a single async result {@link io.vertx.ext.web.client.HttpResponse}.\n\nOn a success result the callback happens after the response has been received\n\n[source,$lang]\n----\n{@link examples.WebClientExamples#receiveResponse(io.vertx.ext.web.client.WebClient)}\n----\n\n[CAUTION]\n====\nBy default, a Vert.x Web Client request ends with an error only if something wrong happens at the network level.\nIn other words, a `404 Not Found` response, or a response with the wrong content type, are *not* considered as failures.\nUse <<http-response-expectations, http response expectations>> if you want the Web Client to perform sanity checks automatically.\n====\n\nWARNING: Responses are fully buffered, use {@link io.vertx.ext.web.codec.BodyCodec#pipe(io.vertx.core.streams.WriteStream)}\nto pipe the response to a write stream\n\n=== Decoding responses\n\nBy default the Web Client provides an http response body as a `Buffer` and does not apply\nany \n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1782537044591}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Preparing Forge Workflow**\n\nI’m focused on preparing a Forge workflow for the issue with the fails-native-image-run. The driver needs to set up additional configurations before generating meaningful coverage. For the Vert.x web-client, using it requires a local Vertx server with the current core dependency, and there's no need for external Docker. However, we must add a system property for a native run due to Netty issues, especially since existing builds include props for version 5.0.0, but not for 5.0.1. What about the dependency on vertx-auth-oauth2? Would it enhance coverage if included?", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0dda688eb9f85d3b016a3f5b4a25348196b5df688a93d7d508\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqP1tU23iKoc6_S5uxD5x2xt2MKLNCHxoLIosxF0fQG1_7W9jj_hn3VWWliSZpMYknybxYInde8gkaEf08rtVMDxgs8I5owRnJOY6yRXYPXhnd_R92PRgCTE7XFNefPG43jF2C3spjv4a7_mmUUEbs_tEnfEgkqkMmGmj-ZdodR12g4YDQUq7U_33atpxKkdUj_ypyetvuyU5KFIv76F1SB6l86gM4zrt2YPDrta9zpK9tRcP7WR-KyD78RmMHJjK3c7A_1d878IQhuG44rHmjwBlkp9EFQpOcIgMG97F_REBhNmnUoLuMQZgaORYTYlETpDDi0ssuLPx6gzjEAoysWhM8GU1HqUymGBj_2JhluX7JTr7QltD_bPRjkszW2x40jwKpT5xtdsiMyR4x5c3UjAI8JkQOBuZZv9h0sotDjn9rCbUI-ZB9h0Qb7zSSBkyKOXdB0jR5t_cXVEVqCiI8Z7tU04DFdxK1vZbLizOWOvidzb8JGlHlLd4tgfy8tZ_9XlXm9UnAAAWg3cODcJHsbY4ExiC-PmJ4SrKHUkxK6lAOrxLDTWrOSnFdXB-3mmE-0I2_qA6-oZ2bxTZPO7KkXUktibdAu9ACE2PV2AASriG5b8qLugNZrxYk5o0Xj27cwe3fztGvM6WMQy0V3OGxv4UCCDPf9ABszbGX5QkmstDqrwbTQxizPmXqZOXwx5VubAJXgn8prrneDmI4gxN_p5n6aTsKLxpEc_w3pobFd_8cLb6B5GyOaDwNqTNuntAZze-npJbsRFV0uXa2qQljELBsP4eLAT8dtJHJgzLdVMzUPAy_fJnpl7IU4pqyPRpS1JPbMWTq6YxbPqgogst8FH3UNwahg6zSsyWum_peDyHoH9mgRSlB0XYDl62e1nMi6o5P2HlLQw4fiobDGa3yAeVICZ4-l3hGLTjGSBR83WaorSq1goDt_NxEyEi5cvW6TJp_n56bw_sKEeWSvYZFuK0m9tzpV1P5xPLIFd7HM8ej3aHsO4Ngw0y--eK9W3mspHV73idOIMB1y5MuuZqGH8-lo6pdcaurfF-E_CgXeTXrLFiyOYni0kA4dxrUn00O5afRE94iyZ5fod9SwIRTO1cb1iel0BibggK-qqwOvi