ially since the user asked about any potential risks. But I wonder if including this dependency would be considered a violation, even though we're not actually selecting it as part of the setup. It's a tricky situation, so I have to be careful with how I present this information.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 is self-contained for meaningful local HTTP client coverage, but it still resolves Netty 4.2.x and needs the same JDK 25 native runtime system properties already used for 5.0.0.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For JDK 25 native-image runtime verification, configure native test runtime system properties for version 5.0.1: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. Meaningful tests can use an in-process Vert.x HttpServer bound to 127.0.0.1 with WebClient/WebClientSession/CachingWebClient, forms, multipart, redirects, cookies, JSON, and streaming; close WebClient, server, and Vertx instances after each test. No external service or Docker image is required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Without the Netty/JDK 25 system properties, native-image run can fail before assertions even if the generated coverage is otherwise meaningful.\",\n    \"OAuth2WebClient is part of the artifact API but full OAuth2 flows reference the optional io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2 dependency; avoid choosing OAuth2-specific coverage unless the workflow intentionally adds that dependency.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0dda688eb9f85d3b016a3f5b68eb68819695daa07cb3acdf23\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2421, "output": 1138, "cacheRead": 27136, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30695, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782537048010, "responseId": "re